  "notes": "Limburgish (Limburgs) — West Germanic (Low Franconian) of the Meuse-Rhenish area. COMMITMENT: this map implements the *Spelling 2003 voor de Limburgse dialecten* (the 'Veldekespelling'), adopted by the Raod veur 't Limburgs and Veldeke-Limburg, using the grapheme->IPA rendering of that system; the norm's own reference variety is Remunjs (Roermond), and the values here are the pan-Limburgish values the norm assigns, not any single village dialect. INPUT CONTRACT: Limburgish text written in Spelling 2003, lowercase, already normalised; Dutch-based or German-based ad-hoc spellings are OUT OF SCOPE and will mis-transcribe. Spelling 2003 is deliberately readable-first: it writes the same sound the same way across dialects, so a grapheme such as <ae> or <ao> stands for the *norm's* vowel, which a given dialect may realise differently. TONE IS NOT REPRESENTED: Limburgish contrasts sleeptoon (dragging tone, Accent 1) with stoottoon (push tone, Accent 2); Spelling 2003 does not write the contrast, so no tonal information can be recovered from the orthography and none is emitted. Mouillering is written with the <j> digraphs (tj, dj, sj, zj, nj, lj).",
